items.title: '32 Custom GAZ...Cosmonaut
items.description:
Lino M posted a photo:

The ’32 Ford, aka The Deuce, has become the most quintessential vehicle for hot rodding and customization. In researching what to do for this month’s challenge called Deuces Wild, I was happy to learn that Russia had a contract with Ford to produce more or less the same vehicle under a different name. That got me thinking about what Russian hot-rodders would do with their rides. I figured it would be a little something like this; striking white and sand blue color scheme, chopped and lowered...part roadster, part lunar rover and all soviet. Here is a ’32 GAZ custom roadster called Cosmonaut.
items.author: nobody@flickr.com ("Lino M")
items.tags: russia russian soviet hot rod car ford gaz 1932 32 roadster space rover lunar moon custom white sand blue lego lino martins lugnuts deuces wild deuce cosmonaut

items.title: CB&Q Class XML-4 24803
items.description:
Chuck Zeiler posted a photo:

Chicago Burlington & Quincy Railroad Class XML-4 24803 at Cicero, Illinois on an unknown day in September 1980, Kodachrome by Chuck Zeiler. The CB&Q built 100 Class XML-4 boxcars at Havelock, Nebraska in 1965, equipped with Keystone cushion underframes and Evans DF Loaded Equipment. They had 10 foot door openings and a 4,974 cubic foot capacity.
items.author: nobody@flickr.com ("Chuck Zeiler")

items.title: CB&Q Class XML-14 23445
items.description:
Chuck Zeiler posted a photo:

Chicago Burlington & Quincy Railroad Class XML-14 23445 at ( I think ) Kansas City, Missouri on an unknown day in May 1980, Kodachrome by Chuck Zeiler. This is one of 200 outside braced boxcars, numbered 23300-23499 classified XML-14, built by CB&Q's shops in Havelock, Nebraska during 1967. The Burlington installed Keystone cushion underframes, Evans bulkheads, and 10 foot sliding doors. The water tower in the background should provide a clue to the location, leave a comment if you recognize the location.
items.author: nobody@flickr.com ("Chuck Zeiler")
items.tags: cbq class xml14 23445 burlington railroad box car boxcar freight chz
